  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Climate Change Programme - Averting water-related emergencies though improved early warning systems</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The scale, severity and frequency of water-related emergencies are increasing due to a climate change impacts.&#xA0;The impacts of these events can be reduced where effective early warning systems (EWS) are in place.
This activity seeks to support PICs to anticipate and prepare for water-related emergencies.&lt;ul&gt;  &lt;li&gt;PICs understand their vulnerability to water-related hazards.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;PICs can anticipate and respond to emerging risks to water related hazards.&lt;/li&gt;  &lt;li&gt;EWS including communications are in place.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;</narrative>
  </description>
